26  import java.nio.CharBuffer;
27  import java.nio.ByteBuffer;
28  import java.nio.charset.Charset;
29  import java.nio.charset.CharsetDecoder;
30  import java.nio.charset.CharsetEncoder;
31  import java.nio.charset.CoderResult;
32  import sun.nio.cs.HistoricallyNamedCharset;
33  import sun.nio.cs.Surrogate;
34  import sun.nio.cs.ext.*;
35  
36  
37  public class IBM933_OLD
38      extends Charset
39      implements HistoricallyNamedCharset
40  {
41  
42      public IBM933_OLD() {
43          super("x-IBM933_Old", null);
44      }
45  
46      public String historicalName() {
47          return "Cp933";
48      }
49  
50      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
51          return (cs instanceof IBM933);
52      }
53  
54      public CharsetDecoder newDecoder() {
55          return new Decoder(this);
56      }
57  
58      public CharsetEncoder newEncoder() {
59          return new Encoder(this);
60      }
61  
62  
63      /**
64       * These accessors are temporarily supplied while sun.io
65       * converters co-exist with the sun.nio.cs.{ext} charset coders
66       * These facilitate sharing of conversion tables between the
67       * two co-existing implementations. When sun.io converters
68       * are made extinct these will be unncessary and should be removed
69       */
70  
71      public String getDecoderSingleByteMappings() {
72          return Decoder.singleByteToChar;
73  
74      }
75  
76      public static short[] getDecoderIndex1() {
77          return Decoder.index1;
78      }
79  
80      public static String getDecoderIndex2() {
81          return Decoder.index2;
82  
83      }
84  
85      public short[] getEncoderIndex1() {
86          return Encoder.index1;
87  
88      }
89      public String getEncoderIndex2() {
90          return Encoder.index2;
91  
92      }
93      public String getEncoderIndex2a() {
94          return Encoder.index2a;
95  
96      }

100         public Decoder(Charset cs) {
101             super(cs);
102             super.mask1 = 0xFFF0;
103             super.mask2 = 0x000F;
104             super.shift = 4;
105             super.singleByteToChar = this.singleByteToChar;
106             super.index1 = this.index1;
107             super.index2 = this.index2;
108         }

2606     protected static class Encoder extends CharsetEncoder {
2607 
2608         private static final char SBase = '\uAC00';
2609         private static final char LBase = '\u1100';
2610         private static final char VBase = '\u1161';
2611         private static final char TBase = '\u11A7';
2612         private static final int  VCount = 21;
2613         private static final int  TCount = 28;
2614         private static final byte G0 = 0;
2615         private static final byte G1 = 1;
2616         private static final byte G2 = 2;
2617         private static final byte G3 = 3;
2618         private byte   charState = G0;
2619         private char   l, v, t;
2620 
2621         private int  mask1;
2622         private int  mask2;
2623         private int  shift;
2624         private static final int SBCS = 0;
2625         private static final int DBCS = 1;
2626         private static final byte SO = 0x0e;
2627         private static final byte SI = 0x0f;
2628         private int byteState;
2629         private int initByteState;
2630 
2631         private final Surrogate.Parser sgp = new Surrogate.Parser();
2632 
2633         public Encoder(Charset cs) {
2634             this(cs, new byte[] {(byte)0x6f}, true);
2635         }
2636 
2637         protected Encoder(Charset cs, byte[] repl, boolean doSBCS) {
2638             super(cs, 2.0f, 4.0f, repl);
2639             mask1 = 0xFFF8;
2640             mask2 = 0x0007;
2641             shift = 3;
2642             initByteState = byteState = doSBCS?SBCS:DBCS;
2643         }
2644 
2645         protected void implReset() {
2646             byteState = initByteState;
2647             charState = G0;
2648         }
2649 
2650         protected CoderResult implFlush(ByteBuffer out) {
2651             if (byteState == DBCS) {
2652                 if (out.remaining() < 1)
2653                     return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2654                 out.put(SI);
2655             }
2656             implReset();
2657             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
2658         }
2659 
2660 
2661         /**
2662          * Returns true if the given character can be converted to the
2663          * target character encoding.
2664          */
2665 
2666         public boolean canEncode(char ch) {
2667            int  index;
2668            int  theBytes;
2669 
2670            index = index1[((ch & mask1) >> shift)] + (ch & mask2);
2671            if (index < 15000)
2672                theBytes = (int)(index2.charAt(index));
2673            else
2674                theBytes = (int)(index2a.charAt(index-15000));
2675 
2676            if (theBytes != 0)
2677                return true;
2678 
2679            // only return true if input char was unicode null - all others are
2680            //    undefined
2681            return( ch == '\u0000');
2682         }

2684         private CoderResult encodeArrayLoop(CharBuffer src, ByteBuffer dst) {
2685             char[] sa = src.array();
2686             int sp = src.arrayOffset() + src.position();
2687             int sl = src.arrayOffset() + src.limit();
2688             byte[] da = dst.array();
2689             int dp = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.position();
2690             int dl = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.limit();
2691             int outputSize = 0;         // size of output
2692             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
2693 
2694             boolean needsFlushing = false;
2695 
2696             try {
2697                 while (sp < sl) {
2698                 char inputChar = sa[sp];
2699 
2700                 // Reject surrogates
2701                 if (sgp.parse(inputChar, sa, sp, sl) < 0)
2702                     return sgp.error();
2703                 if (Surrogate.is(inputChar))
2704                     return sgp.unmappableResult();
2705 
2706                 switch (charState) {
2707                 case G0:
2708                     l = LBase;
2709                     v = VBase;
2710                     t = TBase;
2711 
2712                     if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2713                         l = inputChar;
2714                         charState = G1;
2715                         break;
2716                     }
2717 
2718                     if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2719                         v = inputChar;
2720                         charState = G2;
2721                         break;
2722                     }
2723 
2724                     if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2725                         t = inputChar;
2726                         charState = G3;
2727                         break;
2728                     }
2729 
2730                     break;
2731 
2732                     case G1:
2733                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2734                             l = composeLL(l, inputChar);
2735                             needsFlushing = true;
2736                         break;
2737                         }
2738 
2739                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2740                             v = inputChar;
2741                             charState = G2;
2742                             needsFlushing = true;
2743                             break;
2744                         }
2745 
2746                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2747                             t = inputChar;
2748                             charState = G3;
2749                             needsFlushing = true;
2750                             break;
2751                         }
2752 
2753                         charState = G0;
2754                         break;
2755 
2756                     case G2:
2757                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2758                             needsFlushing = true;
2759 
2760                             l = inputChar;
2761                             v = VBase;
2762                             t = TBase;
2763                             charState = G1;
2764                             break;
2765                         }
2766 
2767                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2768                             needsFlushing = true;
2769                             v = composeVV(l, inputChar);
2770                             charState = G2;
2771                             break;
2772                         }
2773 
2774                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2775                             needsFlushing = true;
2776                             t = inputChar;
2777                             charState = G3;
2778                             break;
2779                         }
2780 
2781                         charState = G0;
2782                         break;
2783 
2784                     case G3:
2785                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2786                             needsFlushing = true;
2787                             t = composeTT(t, inputChar);
2788                             charState = G3;
2789                             break;
2790                         }
2791 
2792                         charState = G0;
2793                         break;
2794                   }
2795 
2796                   if (charState == G0 || sl - sp < 2) {
2797                       int spaceNeeded;
2798                       if (needsFlushing) {
2799                         needsFlushing = false;
2800 
2801                         outputBytes = encodeHangul(composeHangul());
2802 
2803                         if (outputBytes.length == 0) {
2804                             return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
2805                         }
2806 
2807                         if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00) {
2808                             if (byteState == DBCS) {
2809                                 if (dl - dp < 2)
2810                                     return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2811                                 da[dp++] = SI;
2812                             }
2813                             byteState = SBCS;
2814                             spaceNeeded = 1;
2815                         }
2816                         else {
2817                             if (byteState == SBCS) {
2818                                 if (dl - dp < 3) {
2819                                     return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2820                                 }
2821                                 da[dp++] = SO;
2822                             }
2823                             byteState = DBCS;
2824                             spaceNeeded = 2;
2825                         }
2826 
2827                         if (dl - dp < spaceNeeded)
2828                              return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2829                           if (spaceNeeded == 1)
2830                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
2831                           else {
2832                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[0];
2833                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
2834                           }
2835                       }
2836 
2837                       outputBytes = encodeHangul(inputChar);
2838 
2839                       if (outputBytes.length == 0) {
2840                           return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
2841                       }
2842 
2843                       if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00) {
2844                         if (byteState == DBCS) {
2845                             if (dl - dp < 2)
2846                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2847                             da[dp++] = SI;
2848                             byteState = SBCS;
2849                         }
2850                           spaceNeeded = 1;
2851                       } else {
2852                         if (byteState == SBCS) {
2853                             if (dl - dp < 3) {
2854                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2855                             }
2856                             da[dp++] = SO;
2857                             byteState = DBCS;
2858                         }
2859                           spaceNeeded = 2;
2860                       }
2861 
2862                       if (dl - dp < spaceNeeded)
2863                             return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
2864 
2865                       if (spaceNeeded == 1) {
2866                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
2867                       }
2868                       else {
2869                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[0];
2870                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
2871                       }
2872                     }
2873                     // Increment input char position
2874                     sp++;
2875                 }
2876                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
2877             } finally {
2878                 src.position(sp - src.arrayOffset());
2879                 dst.position(dp - dst.arrayOffset());
2880             }
2881         }

2883         private CoderResult encodeBufferLoop(CharBuffer src, ByteBuffer dst) {
2884             int mark = src.position();
2885             int outputSize = 0;
2886             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
2887             boolean needsFlushing = false;
2888 
2889             try {
2890                 while (src.hasRemaining()) {
2891                     char inputChar = src.get();
2892                     if (Surrogate.is(inputChar)) {
2893                         if (sgp.parse(inputChar, src) < 0)
2894                             return sgp.error();
2895                     return sgp.unmappableResult();
2896                     }
2897 
2898                     if (inputChar >= '\uFFFE')
2899                         return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
2900 
2901                     switch (charState) {
2902                     case G0:
2903                         l = LBase;
2904                         v = VBase;
2905                         t = TBase;
2906 
2907                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2908                             l = inputChar;
2909                             charState = G1;
2910                             break;
2911                         }
2912 
2913                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2914                             v = inputChar;
2915                             charState = G2;
2916                             break;
2917                         }
2918 
2919                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2920                             t = inputChar;
2921                             charState = G3;
2922                             break;
2923                         }
2924 
2925                         break;
2926 
2927                         case G1:
2928                             if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2929                                 l = composeLL(l, inputChar);
2930                                 needsFlushing = true;
2931                             break;
2932                             }
2933 
2934                             if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2935                                 v = inputChar;
2936                                 charState = G2;
2937                                 needsFlushing = true;
2938                                 break;
2939                             }
2940 
2941                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2942                                 t = inputChar;
2943                                 charState = G3;
2944                                 needsFlushing = true;
2945                                 break;
2946                             }
2947 
2948                             charState = G0;
2949                             break;
2950 
2951                         case G2:
2952                             if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
2953                                 needsFlushing = true;
2954 
2955                                 l = inputChar;
2956                                 v = VBase;
2957                                 t = TBase;
2958                                 charState = G1;
2959                                 break;
2960                             }
2961 
2962                             if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
2963                                 needsFlushing = true;
2964                                 v = composeVV(l, inputChar);
2965                                 charState = G2;
2966                                 break;
2967                             }
2968 
2969                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2970                                 needsFlushing = true;
2971                                 t = inputChar;
2972                                 charState = G3;
2973                                 break;
2974                             }
2975 
2976                             charState = G0;
2977                             break;
2978 
2979                         case G3:
2980                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
2981                                 needsFlushing = true;
2982                                 t = composeTT(t, inputChar);
2983                                 charState = G3;
2984                                 break;
2985                             }
2986 
2987                             charState = G0;
2988                             break;
2989                       }
2990 
2991                       if (charState == G0 || src.remaining() < 1) {
2992                           int spaceNeeded;
2993 
2994                           if (needsFlushing) {
2995                             needsFlushing = false;
2996 
2997                             outputBytes = encodeHangul(composeHangul());
2998                             if (outputBytes.length == 0) {
2999                                 return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
3000                             }
3001                             if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00) {
3002                                 if (byteState == DBCS) {
3003                                     if (dst.remaining() < 2)
3004                                         return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3005                                     dst.put(SI);
3006                                 }
3007                                 byteState = SBCS;
3008                                 spaceNeeded = 1;
3009                             }
3010                             else {
3011                                 if (byteState == SBCS) {
3012                                     if (dst.remaining() < 3)
3013                                         return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3014                                     dst.put(SO);
3015                                 }
3016                                 byteState = DBCS;
3017                                 spaceNeeded = 2;
3018                             }
3019 
3020                             if (dst.remaining() < spaceNeeded)
3021                                  return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3022                               if (spaceNeeded == 1)
3023                                     dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
3024                               else {
3025                                     dst.put(outputBytes[0]);
3026                                     dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
3027                               }
3028                           }
3029 
3030                           outputBytes = encodeHangul(inputChar);
3031                           if (outputBytes.length == 0) {
3032                                 return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
3033                           }
3034 
3035                           if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00) {
3036                               if (byteState == DBCS) {
3037                                  if (dst.remaining() < 2)
3038                                      return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3039                                  dst.put(SI);
3040                                  byteState = SBCS;
3041                               }
3042                               spaceNeeded = 1;
3043                           } else {
3044                               if (byteState == SBCS) {
3045                                  if (dst.remaining() < 3)
3046                                      return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3047                                  dst.put(SO);
3048                                  byteState = DBCS;
3049                               }
3050                               spaceNeeded = 2;
3051                           }
3052 
3053                           if (dst.remaining() < spaceNeeded)
3054                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
3055 
3056                           if (spaceNeeded == 1)
3057                                 dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
3058                           else {
3059                                 dst.put(outputBytes[0]);
3060                                 dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
3061                             }
3062                         }
3063                       mark++;
3064                 }
3065                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
3066             } finally {
3067                 src.position(mark);
3068             }
3069         }

3071         private char composeHangul() {
3072            int lIndex, vIndex, tIndex;
3073 
3074            lIndex = l - LBase;
3075            vIndex = v - VBase;
3076            tIndex = t - TBase;
3077 
3078            return (char)((lIndex * VCount + vIndex) * TCount + tIndex + SBase);
3079         }
3080 
3081         private char composeLL(char l1, char l2) {
3082            return l2;
3083         }
3084 
3085         private char composeVV(char v1, char v2) {
3086            return v2;
3087         }
3088 
3089         private char composeTT(char t1, char t2) {
3090            return t2;
3091         }

3093         private boolean isLeadingC(char c) {
3094            return (c >= LBase && c <= '\u1159');
3095         }
3096 
3097         private boolean isVowel(char c) {
3098            return (c >= VBase && c <= '\u11a2');
3099         }
3100 
3101         private boolean isTrailingC(char c) {
3102            return (c >= TBase && c <= '\u11f9');
3103         }

3105         protected static byte[] EMPTYBA = new byte[0];
3106         protected byte[] encodeHangul(char unicode) {
3107             int index;
3108             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
3109 
3110             int theBytes;
3111 
3112             // first we convert the unicode to its byte representation
3113             index = index1[((unicode & mask1) >> shift)] + (unicode & mask2);
3114             if (index < 15000)
3115                 theBytes = (int)(index2.charAt(index));
3116             else
3117                 theBytes = (int)(index2a.charAt(index-15000));
3118 
3119             if (theBytes == 0 && unicode != '\u0000')
3120                 return EMPTYBA;
3121 
3122             outputBytes[0] = (byte)((theBytes & 0x0000ff00)>>8);
3123             outputBytes[1] = (byte)(theBytes & 0x000000ff);
3124             return outputBytes;
3125         }
3126 
3127         protected CoderResult encodeLoop(CharBuffer src, ByteBuffer dst) {
3128             if (true && src.hasArray() && dst.hasArray())
3129                 return encodeArrayLoop(src, dst);
3130             else
3131                 return encodeBufferLoop(src, dst);
3132         }
